Author: vlad
Content:
Yep. I know how to navigate google maps, but a zip code textbox, defaulting to the zip code of the ip of the visitor, should be added as soon as possible.

Also, if one accidentally refreshes the page after finding a new location... the map goes right back to California again, which is another huge interface flaw.

Author: Goladus
Content: Apple seems to enjoy a reputation of making stuff that "just works."  They are probably not prepared to guarantee that OS X will "just work" on anything but Apple hardware, and don't want to risk damaging that reputation.
